--- PART 7: MULTIPLICATIVE vs ADDITIVE VIEWS ---
Resonance = multiplicative: qa = +/-b mod p
Co-occurrence = additive: vertices at gap d share cycles
Walsh transform bridges the two!

  p=7, Paley:
    (1,2): a/b=4=3(canon), b-a=1=1(canon), chi(ab)=+1, min_q=3
    (1,3): a/b=5=2(canon), b-a=2=2(canon), chi(ab)=-1, min_q=3
    (2,3): a/b=3=3(canon), b-a=1=1(canon), chi(ab)=-1, min_q=3

  p=11, Paley:
    (1,2): a/b=6=5(canon), b-a=1=1(canon), chi(ab)=-1, min_q=5
    (1,3): a/b=4=4(canon), b-a=2=2(canon), chi(ab)=+1, min_q=3
    (1,4): a/b=3=3(canon), b-a=3=3(canon), chi(ab)=+1, min_q=3
    (1,5): a/b=9=2(canon), b-a=4=4(canon), chi(ab)=+1, min_q=5
    (2,3): a/b=8=3(canon), b-a=1=1(canon), chi(ab)=-1, min_q=3
